InheritParentConfig: true
Checks: >
  -cppcoreguidelines-avoid-do-while,
  -readability-function-cognitive-complexity,
  -clang-analyzer-optin.core.EnumCastOutOfRange,
  -bugprone-unchecked-optional-access,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters

# cppcoreguidelines-avoid-do-while: Catch2 REQUIRE/REQUIRE_FALSE macros expand to do-while loops internally.
# readability-function-cognitive-complexity: Catch2 TEST_CASE macro expansion inflates complexity scores artificially.
# clang-analyzer-optin.core.EnumCastOutOfRange: Catch2 REQUIRE_FALSE macro ORs ResultDisposition::Flags producing value 5 (0x01|0x04), not a declared enumerator — Catch2 internals, not our code.
# bugprone-unchecked-optional-access: Tests use REQUIRE(t.has_value()) before accessing t->field, but tidy cannot see that REQUIRE aborts on failure.
# bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters: StateMachine(float,float) and beep(int,int,int) — API design, suppressed here since tests call both.
